Class ContainerData

  • java.lang.Object
    • au.edu.anu.twcore.data.runtime.TwData
      • au.edu.anu.twcore.ecosystem.runtime.system.ContainerData
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Population, fr.cnrs.iees.properties.PropertyListGetters, fr.cnrs.iees.properties.PropertyListSetters, fr.cnrs.iees.properties.ReadOnlyPropertyList, fr.cnrs.iees.properties.SimplePropertyList, fr.cnrs.iees.properties.SimpleWriteProtectablePropertyList, fr.ens.biologie.generic.DataContainer, fr.ens.biologie.generic.Sizeable, fr.ens.biologie.generic.WriteProtectable, java.lang.Cloneable
    public class ContainerData
extends TwData
implements Population
    A class to contain ComponentContainer automatic data, ie mainly population sizes. This one is for simple containers only ie without nested subContainers. The class is initialized with the internal lists(made immutable) of a Dynamic Container implementation, so that the numbers are always in sync with the collections.
    Author:
    J. Gignoux - 16 avr. 2020
